||<bgcolor='#E0E0FF'>'''Location'''||
||23944 County Road 98, ["Woodland"] (Road 98 & Road 29, Northwest of Davis)||
||<bgcolor='#E0E0FF'>'''Hours'''||
||Opens at 10 AM.  Closes at various hours, from 11 PM to 2 AM, depending on business||
||<bgcolor='#E0E0FF'>'''Phone'''||
||(530) 668-0207 (and be sure to call ahead if you are heading out there late in the evening)||

Sometimes described as "a rural version of Cheers," Plainfield station is a bar-and-grill joint that offers a pleasantly surreal experience for any college student.  It is located in the middle of nowhere, shrouded by trees, a sort of oasis of life and activity.  Besides the bar (no hard liquor is served), they serve reportedly amazing hamburgers and tacos.  With a stage in the roomy backyard, there have been attempts to establish it as the de-facto venue for the Davis area, and ["Music Scene" local bands] have performed here -- but it still remains more or less a bar on the edge of town.

Because Plainfield Station serves food it is legally allowed to let people of all ages in -- But 21 is still the drinking age, obviously.  It has been rumored, however, that many of the bartenders don't check ID...
